column2: Thresholds for assigning 2001 steelhead ages based on length (mm)
YOY length threshold (mm): all fish up to and including the assigned threshold should be classified as YOY; i.e. 80 means 80
Age uncertain: fish that cannot be assign as YOY or Age 1 based on length due to overlap; "none" means that no fish fell into the uncertain category
Age 1+: All fish equal to and above the assigned threshold should be assigned to Age 1+.  i.e., 91 means >= 91.  Note that this may include fish that are older than Age 1
After fish are assigned to age classes, the totals should match the sample sizes listed for each site.  If they don't, then something is amiss.
